HEADWORD: Untreasure
<hw>Un*treas"ure</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>treasure</ets>.]</ety> <def>To bring forth or give
up, as things previously treasured.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The quaintness with
which he <xex>untreasured</xex>, as by rote, the stores of his
memory.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J. Mitford.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untreasured</ent>⟦br⟧
